# --- Line endings -----------------------------------------------------------
# Store text as LF in the repo and check it out as LF everywhere. This stops the
# endless "LF will be replaced by CRLF" warnings and the phantom modified/deleted
# files that came from CRLF round-tripping between Windows and the scrapers.
* text=auto eol=lf

# --- Generated data ---------------------------------------------------------
# These files are rewritten in full by the daily scrape, so they should never be
# hand-merged. `merge=ours` auto-resolves them on pull/rebase (keeping whichever
# side we're building on); the next scrape refreshes them regardless. This is
# what removes the recurring events.json / archive.json conflicts.
public/data/events.json          merge=ours
public/data/archive.json         merge=ours
public/data/scraped_venues.json  merge=ours
public/data/warnings.json        merge=ours
public/data/health.json          merge=ours

